README - FLTK Dock Version 0.07
-------------------------------


WHAT IS FLTK Dock?

     FLTK Dock is a dockable window framework for Fast Light Tool Kit
     (FLTK). FLTK Dock (pronounced "fulltick dock") provides advance,
     customizable toolbar and window with docking, floating and other
     functionalities of latest dockable-floatable windows for general
     desktop application.


     For more information visit http://fltkdock.sourceforge.net and
     FLTK Home http://www.fltk.org


BUILD INSTRUCTIONS

     Make sure that the FLTK library version 2 is installed on your 
     system. Otherwise you can get it from http://www.fltk.org

     ./configure
     make
     make install

     Options that you can pass to ./configure include:

         --enable-debug          - Enable debugging code & symbols
         --enable-shared         - Enable generation of shared libraries


     To install the library, become root and type "make install".
     The header files to "includedir"/fltk, and the library files 
     to "libdir".


REPORTING BUGS

     To report a bug in FLTK Dock, send an email to "z_hossain@users.sf.net",
     or use bug tracking system at sourceforge. Please include the FLTK 
     version, FLTK Dock version, operating system & version, and compiler
     name that you are using.


